.TH "do_fw_call_smc" 9 "do_fw_call_smc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
do_fw_call_smc \- Call system-level platform management layer (SMC)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" do_fw_call_smc
.BI "(u64 arg0 "  ","
.BI "u64 arg1 "  ","
.BI "u64 arg2 "  ","
.BI "u32 *ret_payload "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "arg0" 12
Argument 0 to SMC call
.IP "arg1" 12
Argument 1 to SMC call
.IP "arg2" 12
Argument 2 to SMC call
.IP "ret_payload" 12
Returned value array
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Invoke platform management function via SMC call (no hypervisor present).
.SH "RETURN"
Returns status, either success or error+reason
